import GPy
import pymc3 as pm
from theano import tensor as tt
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from data.get_results import get_results
from likelihood import get_kernel
from acquisitions import softmax_ucb, generate, likelihood

In [2]:
results = get_results('data/results.json').iloc[3:]
function_names = results['function_name'].unique()
kernel_dict = {f: get_kernel(results, GPy.kern.RBF(1), f) for f in function_names}
functions_dict = results[['function_name', 'function']].drop_duplicates(subset = ['function_name']).set_index('function_name').to_dict()['function']
normalized_functions_dict = {f: np.array(functions_dict[f]) / np.std(functions_dict[f]) for f in function_names}

Simulate actions with negative quadratic reward¶

In [3]:
neg_quad = normalized_functions_dict['neg_quad']
neg_quad_kern = kernel_dict['neg_quad']
fmax = np.argmax(neg_quad)
In [4]:
plt.plot(neg_quad);
plt.axvline(x=fmax, ls='--', c='black');

Simulate actions with pure explore, pure exploit, and balanced strategies and different temperature parameters¶

In [5]:
explore_params = [1., 0., .5]
temp_params = [.00001, .0001, .001, .01]

data = [[generate(softmax_ucb, {'explore': [explore_params[i]], 'temperature': [temp_params[j]]}, neg_quad_kern, neg_quad, 20, 10, 1, [1.])[0]
            for i in range(len(explore_params))] for j in range(len(temp_params))]
In [6]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(temp_params), len(explore_params), sharex=True, sharey=True, figsize=(15,10))
for j in range(len(temp_params)):
    for i in range(len(explore_params)):
        actions = data[j][i][:,:,4].argmax(axis=2)
        axes[j][i].plot(actions[:5].T);
        axes[j][i].axhline(y=fmax, ls='--', c='black');
In [7]:
for j in range(len(temp_params)):
    for i in range(len(explore_params)):
        
        with pm.Model() as model:
            explore = pm.Beta('explore', 1., 1.)
            temperature = pm.Gamma('temperature', .1, .1)
            obs = pm.Potential('obs', likelihood(data[j][i], softmax_ucb, {'explore': explore, 'temperature': temperature}, 1, [1.], c=100))
            trace = pm.sample(200)
        
        print ("Explore: {0}, Temperature: {1}".format(str(explore_params[i]), str(temp_params[j])))
        pm.traceplot(trace);
        plt.show();
